OL,4,Cgiven #500,000 to secure future
OL,6,FLocated next to the headland, the
OL,7,FHeugh battery played a key role on 16
OL,8,FDecember 1914, when the town was
OL,9,Fbombarded by German warships.
OL,11,FIt went down in history as Britain's
OL,12,Fonly battlefield of the First World War
OL,14,FTom Gledhill, from Historic England,
OL,15,Fsaid: "It's such an important site
OL,16,Ffrom the point of view of recording
OL,17,Fhistory and remembering the history of
OL,18,Fthe First World War. It's really
OL,19,Fimportant to keep this place open to
OL,20,Fvisitors."
