OL,6,FAt least 130 people were killed during
OL,7,Fthe battle on 16 December 1914, with
OL,8,Fhundreds more injured.
OL,10,FDr Michael Reeve from the Open
OL,11,FUniversity said: "It was very
OL,12,Fdevastating. You've got the shock that
OL,13,Fthis could even happen and the enemy
OL,14,Fcould fire on the town."
OL,16,FScarborough was also affected by
OL,17,FGerman bombardment but just 15 people
OL,18,Fdied.
