OL,6,F"They showed us his medals, what he
OL,7,Fwas doing, which gun he was stationed
OL,8,Fat, who he was with on the day. It's
OL,9,Famazing that we've got this facility
OL,10,Fhere to keep his history and the story
OL,11,Fof the bombardment alive."
OL,13,FIan Lightfoot's family members were
OL,14,Fone of many sheltering from the
OL,15,Fbombardment.
OL,17,F"They were all huddled in the cellar,"
OL,18,Fhe explained. "There was the mother,
OL,19,Fmy grandmother her little brother and
OL,20,Fher two sisters.
